f(x) = \sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{1}{1+k^4 (x-k^2)^2}.
\int_{x=0}^\infty \sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{dx}{1+k^4(x-k^2)^2} = \sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{\pi + 2 \tan^{-1} k^4}{2k^2} < \pi \sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{1}{k^2} = \frac{\pi^3}{6}.
